/// eo9:fs-eofs — the eofs provider world (plan/14-eofs.md, milestone 2).
///
/// `fs.eofs` imports a raw block device (`eo9:disk/disk`) and exports `eo9:fs/fs` backed
/// by Eo9's native filesystem (`crates/eofs-core`): copy-on-write, Merkle-hashed,
/// lz4-compressed, snapshotting. The same provider component runs over any disk —
/// `disk.mem $ fs.eofs $ program` in usermode today, a file-backed or virtio disk later —
/// because all I/O goes through the imported disk capability.
///
/// There is no configure interface: the documented default behaviour is to mount the
/// disk if it already carries an eofs image and to format a blank (all-zero uberblock
/// slots) disk in place, so the unconfigured provider never traps (plan/09 Decision 14).
package eo9:fs-eofs@0.1.0;

world eofs {
    import eo9:disk/disk@0.1.0;
    export eo9:fs/fs@0.1.0;
}
